description.narrative:
Project Title: Gender Integrated Healthcare and Women Empowerment&nbsp;
This program aims to promote gender equality in target rural areas, and it well accords with addressing of women&rsquo;s inequalities and harmoniously contribute to implementing of CEDAW as a member of CSOs and to cover women empowerment and health issues particularly Sexual and Reproductive Health &amp; Rights (SRHR) and Basic Healthcare Services for women. In addition, the issues on VAW (Violence Against Women) will also be addressed along with changes in conditions of women in later time.&nbsp;
Objective: Increased Access to Sexual and Reproductive Health (SRH) &amp; Basic Healthcare Services for Women in (20) remote villages in (5) Townships
Problem Analysis: The major problems associated with health issues root in poor health care services and facilities provided by government as well as lacking of full coverage by health personnel/staffs in those areas where accessibility is limited. Health education, Sexual and Reproductive health rights and personal hygiene practices level in target villages are considerably low and then lacking of health workers to provide knowledge in these communities become key problems to address through this project.
Expected Result : To cover health issues particularly primary health education and reproductive health and rights, skills training for women empowerment. Equipping knowledge and capacity building include CEDAW and its articles, gender concepts and dimensions, and gender based violence (GBV) issues. In addition, the issues and concerns on GBV (Gender Based Violence) will also be promoted and addressed along with changes in conditions of women.
As a part of direct implementation, primary health care trainings, sexual reproductive health and rights special talks and awareness raising on gender and GBV will be provided in each target community.
